  "text": "The open string spectrum of the Liouville BCFT for FZZT boundary conditions is known to have the usual primaries {e αφ }, of dimension h α = α(Q − α) (note the factor of two difference with respect to the bulk primaries (2.12)). As usual in Liouville field theory, the continuum spectrum α = Q/2 + iP corresponds to delta-function normalizable states, while real exponents α ≤ Q/2 correspond to local operators and are used in the dressing of the matter primaries. In the following, we set the bulk cosmological constant µ = 0 and keep µ i B = 0. A crucial observation, due to Distler [CITATION_1] , is that Liouville and c = −2 matter can be formally combined into a βγ bosonic ghost system of conformal dimensions (2, −1),",
